{
  "stem": "17135.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then when-- when-- when the order came-- interesting enough, when the order came from Berlin to evacuate Auschwitz, my lagerfuhrer, the former cooking-- kitchen chief-- listen to what he did-- took a truck and he said, let's go in Auschwitz the place where they stored all the individual private things of newcomers-- were stored called Canada, for some reason, because Canada was the symbol-- Canada is everything.",
      "word_count": 68
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Canada is [? gorgeous ?] to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this man went with a truck, and took me with the truck, and another have-- inmate to-- to go to Canada and whatever you can use to take back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was so corrupt-- that's only with [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Corrupt to the core.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then he took the truck to Buna, to the camp where-- where I was before, because he knew the current commandant was a friend of his.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were already all organized, standing, waiting to march out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and-- I told him, can you leave me here?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- we are going to be evacuated, and OK, stay here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I stayed there with my former friends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There's another interesting story.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have to tell you what happened in-- in Buna, because it's very unusual.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They sent to Buna in 1943 there about three groups of young people [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Do you know what [HEBREW] is?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Preparing for aliyah to Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were in farms, and they worked them-- they were on the farm, and they worked for the Germans, for the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then in '42 and '43, they decided even them to deport to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And those groups came, there were three groups of 20, 30 kids, and they organized within the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They lived like in a kibbutz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They helped each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
